						               													<description>Partial description from www.thaiboardgame.net&amp;#10;&amp;#10;After being seen on screen and various computer games, Kantana had decided to release a collectible card game based on their first Thai 3D animation - Khan Kluay The Card Game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The CCG is now available in various toy stores and card game stores, with the price of 35 bath per booster box. A booster box come with a game manual and 5 random cards. There are overall 70 unique cards for player to collect, ranging from common, uncommon and rare.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;                                                        &amp;#10;                                                    &amp;#10;                                                &amp;#10;                                            &amp;#10;                                        &amp;#10;                                    &amp;#10;                                &amp;#10;                            &amp;#10;                        &amp;#10;                    &amp;#10;                &amp;#10;            &amp;#10;        &amp;#10;    &amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Deck construction must have at least 30 cards and contain only 3 duplicate cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are 2 card types: Character Cards and Event Cards&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are 5 zones for each player in the game&amp;#10;- Battle Field: The character battle here.&amp;#10;- Army zone: play a card face down in this zone that card cannot be played until the end of the game. Only a card can be played in this zone each turn.&amp;#10;- Draw pile&amp;#10;- Graveyard: All defeated character and used event card will put in here.&amp;#10;- Discard pile: The card that put directly from the draw pile will put to this zone.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Step of the game: Each turn, player follow these steps: draw a card - play cards - battle - end(check maximum hand)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Objective of the game is eliminate all opponent's characters and attack him/her directly that can force him/her to put cards directly to the discard piles. The game's end when the cards in discard pile reach the limit.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Rock-paper-scissor rule can add the attack and defend point in the battle.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
